Q: How to access the result payload after calling CodeIgniter&#39;s query() method A: <p>I hope this change will helps you</p>

<pre><code>$query = $this-&gt;db-&gt;query("SELECT * FROM mytable;");
$data = $query-&gt;result();
return $data;
</code></pre>

<p>you can rewrite this query in other ways</p>

<pre><code>$this-&gt;db-&gt;select('*');
$this-&gt;db-&gt;from('mytable');
$data=$this-&gt;db-&gt;get();
</code></pre>

<p>for data result</p>

<pre><code>return $data-&gt;result();
</code></pre>

<p>for number of rows</p>

<pre><code> return $data-&gt;num_rows();
</code></pre>
